o and TV presenter\n*[[7 April]] - [[Duncan James]], singer ([[Blue (boy band)|Blue]])\n*[[9 April]] - [[Rachel Stevens]], singer ([[S Club 7]])\n*[[28 April]] - [[Lauren Laverne]], singer, radio DJ and TV presenter\n*[[4 May]] - [[Matthew Rose (bass)|Matthew Rose]], bass\n*[[22 May]] - [[Jordan (model)|Jordan]], model and would-be singer\n*[[6 June]] - [[Sophie Solomon]], violinist\n*[[27 June]] - [[Lolly (singer)|Lolly]], singer\n*[[4 July]] - [[Stephen McNally (musician)|Stephen McNally]], English singer-songwriter ([[BBMak]])\n*[[15 September]] - [[David Sneddon]], singer-songwriter\n*[[9 October]] - [[Nicky Byrne]], Irish singer ([[Westlife]])\n*[[27 November]] - [[Mike Skinner (musician)|Mike Skinner]], rapper, musician and record producer\n*[[18 December]] - [[Lindsay Armaou]], Greek-born Irish-based singer ([[B*Witched]])\n\n==Deaths==\n*[[11 January]] - [[William John Edwards]], Cerdd Dant singer (b. 1898)\n*[[15 January]] - [[Jack Jackson (British radio)|Jack Jackson]], trumpeter, bandleader and radio disc jockey (b. 1906)\n*[[24 February]] - [[Mrs Mills]], pianist (b. 1918)\n*[[9 March]] - [[L. Radley Flynn]], singer and actor (b. 1902)\n*[[12 March]] - [[Tolchard Evans]], songwriter, composer, pianist and bandleader (b. 1901)\n*[[3 April]] - [[Ray Noble (musician)|Ray Noble]], composer and bandleader (b. 1903)\n*[[21 April]] - [[Sandy Denny]], singer ([[Fairport Convention]]) (b. 1947) (cerebral haemorrhage)\n*[[14 August]] - [[Victor Silvester]], dance band leader (b. 1900)\n*[[7 September]]\n**<!--September 7-->[[Keith Moon]], drummer for [[The Who]] (b. 1946) ([[Clomethiazole]] overdose)\n**<!--September 7-->[[Charles Williams (composer)|Charles Williams]], composer (b. 1893)\n*[[15 September]] - [[Edmund Crispin|Robert Bruce Montgomery]], composer (b. 1921)\n*[[13 November]] - [[W. S. Gwynn Williams]], musician and composer (b. 1896)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[1978 in British radio]]\n* [[1978 in British television]]\n* [[1978 in the United Kingdom]]\n* 